==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Universal grammar
<hw>U`ni*ver"sal gram"mar</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Linguistics)</fld> <def>the principles forming the basis for the
human ability to understand language.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Linguistics)</fld> <def>the general properties and
constraints common to all human languages; also, the study of such
principles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Universalian</ent>⟦br⟧
